commentary: Rashid Khan to Liton Das, OUT oh geez. The very next ball, a shot that typifies his career. Another full ball at off stump, ripping away late after drifting. He's looked to sweep. Not a safe option against Rashid and you'd think he knew that going by the last ball. Top edge hangs up and slip takes it with a couple of steps to his right. A poor, poor shot to end an impressive innings

commentary: Rashid Khan to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT direct hit from Shenwari and Shakib is gone! Oh this is disastrous for Bangladesh. Poor judgement from Shakib. Got back to a googly, flicked it to Shenwari's left at midwicket and just took off without a call. Mushfiqur saw no run there and he stood his ground. Shakib slipped as he looked to turn when he realised this and was nowhere in the picture as this throw came in one the bounce to take out the stumps. Mushfiqur had taken a couple of steps down, but it doesn't appear that either of them had made a call

commentary: Rashid Khan to Imrul Kayes, OUT looks like Mushfiqur could be run out at the non-striker's end! It hinges on whether Rashid knocked the stumps out with his hips...looks like the tricep and elbow area on slow-mo replay. He has the ball in his hand so this will go his way! Mushfiqur Rahim is gone. Rashid picked up the throw from the leg side in front of the stumps and was falling backwards as he collected the throw and looked to take out the stumps. As a result there was some element of him falling onto the stumps but in the end it is all clean. The hip was nowhere close to the stumps. But once again, atrocious running. Kayes had blocked this googly into the square leg region. He didn't want the run. Mushfiq was past halfway because he wanted it. Had no chance of making it back. Once again, no calling.

A dive to his right to stop Shahzad's cut first of all and then, despite not having the ball in his hand, a quick recovery to pick up chuck the stumps down with his throwing arm. There was no run there, more so with Shahzad as his partner. Poor judgement from Rahmat

commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza to Samiullah Shinwari, SIX runs clatters it over long-on! What a shot. This is a slow pitch, remember, so it takes some hitting to swipe from under a length ball and clear the leg side. But Shenwari has done exactly that. A clean hit to a ball with some width outside off
